      "title": "57 AI billionaires are worth $320 billion combined",
      "content_html": "<a href=\"https://boingboing.net/2026/07/03/57-ai-billionaires-are-worth-320-billion-combined.html\" rel=\"nofollow\" title=\"57 AI billionaires are worth $320 billion combined\"><img alt=\"&quot;Billionaire wealth&quot; by Wikideas1 is marked with CC0 1.0. To view the terms, visit https://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/deed.en.\" class=\"webfeedsFeaturedVisual wp-post-image\" height=\"595\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/boingboing.net/wp-content/uploads/2026/07/toohey-1115883.jpg?fit=1200%2C595&amp;quality=60&amp;ssl=1\" style=\"display: block; margin: auto; margin-bottom: 5px;\" width=\"1200\" /></a><p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">A new analysis from <a href=\"https://futuresearch.ai/ai-researcher-net-worth/\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" target=\"_blank\">FutureSearch's wealth study of AI billionaires</a> counts 57 AI billionaires worldwide, worth a combined $320 billion — and almost none of that fortune has anything to do with a PhD. Chip designer Chen Tianshi of Cambricon Technologies tops the list at $40 billion, followed by OpenAI president Greg Brockman ($28 billion) and DeepSeek founder Liang Wenfeng ($27 billion). &#8212; <a class=\"read-more\" href=\"https://boingboing.net/2026/07/03/57-ai-billionaires-are-worth-320-billion-combined.html\">Read the rest </a></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://boingboing.net/2026/07/03/57-ai-billionaires-are-worth-320-billion-combined.html\">57 AI billionaires are worth $320 billion combined</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://boingboing.net\">Boing Boing</a>.</p>",
